Assistant:One use of `MPI_Barrier` is for example to control access to an external resource such as the filesystem, which is not accessed using MPI. For example, if you want each process to write stuff to a file in sequence, you could do it like this:

```
int rank, size;
MPI_Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &rank);
MPI_Comm_size(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &size);
for ( int ii = 0; ii < size; ++ii ) {
    if ( rank == ii ) {
        // my turn to write to the file
        writeStuffToTheFile();
    }
    MPI_Barrier(MPI_COMM_WORLD);
}

```

That way, you can be sure that no two processes are concurrently calling `writeStuffToTheFile`.

