Assistant:Well, instead of N loops - you just need one. Within this main loop you have to have just two inner loops for incrementing array of indices and for printing values:

```
int increment(int* index, int N, int len)
{
    for (int i = N - 1; i >= 0; --i)
    {
        ++index[i];
        if (index[i] < len)
            return 1;
        index[i] = 0;
    }
    return 0;   
}

```

So - the main loop:

```
    int index[N] = {};

    do
    {
        // print
        for (int i = 0; i < N; ++i)
            printf("%c", arr[index[i]]);
        printf("\n");
    } while (increment(index, N, len));

```

